      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "In Europe, there's a wide array of beauty standards due to the continent's diversity. Key features generally include a well-rounded face, fair skin, and, though changing, a high facial hair growth rate for men and a preference for more androgynous figures. In East Asia, smooth skin, an oval face shape, and a more pronounced, Asian curvature of the face are highly appreciated. It's important to note the recent move toward Westernization in some East Asian markets. In African populations, skin often features an expanded nose, fuller lips, smaller eyes, and a V-shaped face, with very fair skin and facial hair reducing over generations. As you can see, these features can vary greatly by region and are furthermore subject to change due to modernization and western influence. It's also crucial to revisit local diversity and avoid overgeneralizing within these areas. When it comes to informing your design team, it's always a good idea to focus on a balanced representation of figures while also allowing for a range of beauty ideals within each demographic.",
